[Re: ProMED-mail Cholera, diarrhea & dysentery update (32): Africa, Asia, Europe 20151027.3746833]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Is there any new information about the suspected case of cholera on the island of Kos mentioned in the [ProMED-mail posting referenced above]?

--
Heinz Dewald
Health Department
Merzig-Wadern
Germany
<h.dewald@merzig-wadern.de>

[The initial news report stated: "An official for the Centre for Disease Control and Prevention told Reuters a 79-year-old Dutch tourist was transferred from Kos for tests and treatment in an Athens hospital with symptoms of cholera, including bad diarrhea and high fever, but the diagnosis was not yet confirmed."

ProMED-mail would like more information on this case, which is likely not to be cholera because high fever has been reported (rare in cholera) and it was in a Dutch tourist, not a refugee. Cases of cholera imported into the developed world rarely lead to secondary cases as a functioning sanitation system and the availability of clean water would prevent transmission. Person to person transmission of cholera is not at all common. - Mod.LL

Maps of Greece can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/greece/maps/greece-map.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3755455,48504. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
